WEBVTT

00:03.291 --> 00:05.083
♪ OHHH OHHH OHHH ♪

00:07.333 --> 00:10.208
(Joss Stone's
"Could Have Been You" playing)

00:10.250 --> 00:12.041
♪ BAH BAH BAH, YEAH ♪

00:12.083 --> 00:14.291
HEY.
HEY.

00:14.333 --> 00:16.500
♪ OH, OH ♪

00:16.542 --> 00:19.375
SO PETE MUST BE HAPPY.

00:19.417 --> 00:22.000
♪ OH, IT'S A SHAME,
WE USED TO BE SO TIGHT ♪

00:22.041 --> 00:24.000
WHAT?

00:24.041 --> 00:27.041
CUSTODY OF LUCAS.
OH.

00:27.083 --> 00:29.250
YEAH, YEAH, I THINK SO.
I MEAN...

00:29.291 --> 00:31.250
I GUESS.
WELL, HE WON, RIGHT?

00:31.291 --> 00:34.333
(chuckles) YEAH.
HE WON.

00:34.375 --> 00:36.333
(door opens)
SAM...

00:36.375 --> 00:38.250
(Pete) YOU COMING TO BED?

00:38.291 --> 00:41.875
♪ ...WITHOUT IT,
THERE'S NO GAIN, ONLY PAIN ♪

00:41.917 --> 00:46.041
YEAH. I, UM...
I'LL BE IN IN A MINUTE.

00:46.083 --> 00:47.750
♪ ...ON THE SHELF ♪

00:47.792 --> 00:50.333
♪ I'LL GIVE MY LOVE
TO SOMEONE ELSE ♪

00:50.375 --> 00:52.375
♪ IF YOU SEE ME WALKING BY ♪

00:52.417 --> 00:54.583
♪ HAND IN HAND
WITH ANOTHER GUY ♪

00:54.625 --> 00:56.041
♪ KNOW THAT IT'S TRUE ♪

00:56.083 --> 00:58.041
♪ OOH, OOH ♪
♪ IT COULD'VE BEEN YOU ♪

00:58.083 --> 00:59.500
(breathless) MY GOD.

00:59.542 --> 01:02.041
(exhales deeply) WE WERE
SUPPOSED TO JUST HAVE DINNER

01:02.083 --> 01:04.583
LIKE NORMAL PEOPLE.
WE ATE.

01:04.625 --> 01:06.041
(pants) I ATE.

01:06.083 --> 01:07.834
COOPER.

01:07.875 --> 01:09.208
DO YOU...

01:09.250 --> 01:12.041
DO YOU THINK WE SHOULD
TALK ABOUT WHAT THIS MEANS?

01:12.083 --> 01:13.667
YOU THINK IT MEANS SOMETHING?

01:13.709 --> 01:15.041
DO YOU?

01:15.083 --> 01:17.041
YOU WANT
TO JUST DO IT AGAIN?

01:17.083 --> 01:18.667
OKAY.

01:18.709 --> 01:20.166
MM.

01:20.208 --> 01:23.000
♪ OH ♪
♪ DON'T WANNA WAIT ♪

01:24.709 --> 01:27.208
HEY. I THOUGHT YOU HAD
THE DAY OFF TODAY.

01:27.250 --> 01:29.834
UH, YEAH. UH, MAYA'S GOT
A HISTORY EXAM TOMORROW,

01:29.875 --> 01:32.417
SO I'M DOING
HER ULTRASOUND TODAY.
OH, YOU'RE SO SWEET.

01:32.458 --> 01:35.208
I JUST GOT
SOME REALLY GOOD NEWS.
OH, GOD. OH, NO.

01:35.250 --> 01:37.500
WHAT?
THE BITCH IS BACK.

01:37.542 --> 01:39.875
THE WOMAN WHO THREW THE CUP
OF COFFEE AT MY HEAD?
YEAH.

01:39.917 --> 01:41.875
SHE'S HERE?
SHE'S WAITING FOR ME
IN MY OFFICE

01:41.917 --> 01:43.250
WITH HER HUSBAND RIGHT NOW.

01:43.291 --> 01:44.875
GOD. WHY THEY'D EVEN BOTHER

01:44.917 --> 01:47.875
TO DO MARRIAGE COUNSELING AGAIN
AFTER LAST YEAR...

01:47.917 --> 01:51.041
YOU KNOW SHE CALLS THAT
POOR SWEET MAN THE WEASEL?

01:51.083 --> 01:53.041
VIOLET, SHE THREW
A COFFEE CUP AT MY HEAD.

01:53.083 --> 01:54.625
I HAVE A SCAR.

01:54.667 --> 01:56.625
(laughs)
SHE'S GOT ANGER ISSUES.
YEAH.

01:56.667 --> 01:59.667
(elevator bell dings)
YOU KNOW, I MEAN, DEEP,
UNRESOLVED ANGER ISSUES.

01:59.709 --> 02:02.458
OH! (laughs) LOOK AT YOU.

02:02.500 --> 02:04.709
I KNOW. CRAZY, HUH?

02:04.750 --> 02:07.333
YOUR MOM'S ON HER WAY UP.
YOU READY?
OH, YOU WERE GONNA
TELL ME SOMETHING?

02:07.375 --> 02:10.000
I'LL TELL YOU LATER.

02:13.291 --> 02:16.041
ARE YOU STILL, UH,
NOT TALKING TO ME?

02:16.083 --> 02:18.583
OKAY. I HAD SEX
WITH CHARLOTTE LAST NIGHT.

02:18.625 --> 02:20.583
IT WAS SUPPOSED
TO BE JUST DINNER,

02:20.625 --> 02:24.542
BUT IT BECAME DINNER WITH SEX.
I DON'T KNOW WHAT TO DO.

02:24.583 --> 02:26.542
I HAD TO DO IT, VIOLET.

02:26.583 --> 02:29.041
I COULDN'T LIE ON THE STAND.
COME ON, REALLY?

02:29.083 --> 02:32.083
I NEED TO TALK TO YOU.
TALK TO SOMEBODY ELSE.

02:36.375 --> 02:38.625
H-HELLO?

02:38.667 --> 02:41.583
DR. TURNER?

02:41.625 --> 02:44.333
IT IS SO GOOD
TO SEE YOU. MM.

02:44.375 --> 02:47.333
OH. IT'S GREAT
TO SEE YOU, TOO, CLAIRE.
(laughs)

02:47.375 --> 02:48.959
UM...

02:49.000 --> 02:51.125
(laughs) YEAH.

02:52.875 --> 02:54.208
SHE'S HAPPY.

02:54.250 --> 02:56.041
YES, I CAN SEE THAT.

02:56.083 --> 02:57.583
NO, I MEAN, REALLY HAPPY.

02:57.625 --> 02:59.917
IRWIN THINKS
I HAVE DEMENTIA.
SWEETIE,
I DON'T THINK THAT.

02:59.959 --> 03:02.083
IT'S JUST, YOU'RE USUALLY
NOT A HAPPY PERSON,

03:02.125 --> 03:03.709
AND YOU CHANGED,
JUST OVERNIGHT.

03:03.750 --> 03:06.208
SOMETHING'S WRONG.
OH, JUST SAY IT, IRWIN.

03:06.250 --> 03:08.667
COME ON, SAY IT.
I WAS A BITCH. (laughs)

03:08.709 --> 03:10.041
RIGHT, DR. TURNER?

03:10.083 --> 03:12.125
IT'S OKAY.
I WAS A HUGE BITCH.

03:12.166 --> 03:13.875
(laughs) RIGHT?

03:13.917 --> 03:16.959
BUT I AM NOT ANYMORE.
I'M FEELING BETTER.

03:17.000 --> 03:18.792
AND I'M DOING CHARITY WORK.

03:18.834 --> 03:20.458
THAT'S--THAT'S WONDERFUL.

03:20.500 --> 03:22.458
SHE GAVE AWAY
ALL OF OUR MONEY...
UH-HUH.

03:22.500 --> 03:24.458
TO A CHURCH.
DIDN'T NEED IT.

03:24.500 --> 03:27.458
AND NOW SHE'S--WELL, WE'RE
HAVING A LOT OF SEX NOW.
YOU THINK HE'D BE THRILLED.

03:27.500 --> 03:29.333
I AM, I AM. I...
IT'S NOT HER.

03:29.375 --> 03:30.959
YOU KNOW MY WIFE.

03:31.000 --> 03:32.959
WELL, UH, C-CLAIRE,
HOW WOULD YOU EXPLAIN

03:33.000 --> 03:36.333
THIS, UH, T-TRANSFORMATION?

03:36.375 --> 03:39.959
I CAN FEEL HIM IN MY SOUL...

03:40.000 --> 03:42.041
INSIDE ME.

03:42.083 --> 03:44.000
GOD.

03:44.041 --> 03:45.625
I HAVE FOUND GOD.

03:45.667 --> 03:50.041
I HAVE BEEN TOUCHED
BY THE HAND OF GOD.

03:56.083 --> 03:57.667
(elevator bell dings)

03:57.709 --> 04:00.000
STOP STARING AT ME
LIKE I'M ABOUT TO KEEL OVER.

04:00.041 --> 04:01.375
(chuckles) I'M FINE.

04:01.417 --> 04:04.000
I JUST--I JUST WISH
YOU WOULDN'T BE SO STUBBORN.

04:04.041 --> 04:06.792
YOU KNOW,
YOU NEED TO BE RESTING.
I'LL REST LATER.

04:06.834 --> 04:08.166
HEY, GUYS.
PETE.

04:08.208 --> 04:10.166
WILLIAM, GOOD TO SEE YOU.
HOW YOU FEELING?

04:10.208 --> 04:13.291
OH, LET'S JUST SAY
I'M GLAD TO BE HOME.

04:13.333 --> 04:15.333
UH... IF YOU'LL EXCUSE ME,

04:15.375 --> 04:17.959
I HAVE SOME WORK TO DO
IN MY OFFICE.

04:18.000 --> 04:19.875
OKAY.

04:22.333 --> 04:25.542
THE FLIGHT FROM SWITZERLAND
REALLY TOOK

04:25.583 --> 04:27.709
A LOT OUT OF HIM.

04:27.750 --> 04:30.250
IS THERE ANYTHING I CAN DO?

04:30.291 --> 04:32.875
UH, I'M CONSULTING WITH
SOME A-LIST SPECIALISTS,

04:32.917 --> 04:35.291
SEE IF THERE'S SOMETHING ELSE
THAT WE CAN TRY.

04:35.333 --> 04:37.041
HE HAS TO KEEP FIGHTING.

04:37.083 --> 04:40.458
I CAN'T LET HIM GIVE UP,
NOT NOW.

04:40.500 --> 04:44.041
WELL, THAT'S WHAT YOU WANT.
WHAT ABOUT WHAT HE WANTS?

04:44.083 --> 04:48.083
I THINK
HE'S COME BACK TO DIE.

04:48.125 --> 04:50.083
(woman speaking indistinctly
over p.a.)

04:50.125 --> 04:52.041
(footsteps approach,
door opens)

04:52.083 --> 04:54.583
THANK YOU. HELLO.
I'M DR. MONTGOMERY.

04:54.625 --> 04:57.041
HI, I'M GEORGE WALTERS.
THIS IS MY DAUGHTER KIM.

04:57.083 --> 04:58.542
HI, KIM. THE E.R. DOCTOR

04:58.583 --> 05:00.542
SAYS YOU'RE HAVING
A LOT OF BACK PAIN.

05:00.583 --> 05:02.542
IT STARTED
A FEW DAYS AGO.

05:02.583 --> 05:04.875
IT SAYS HERE
YOU'RE AT 30 WEEKS.

05:04.917 --> 05:07.125
YOU HAVEN'T HAD
ANY PRENATAL CARE?
WE LIVE ON A FARM.

05:07.166 --> 05:09.875
IT'S DIFFICULT FOR US
TO GET INTO THE CITY.
OKAY.

05:09.917 --> 05:12.041
UH, WELL, LET'S TAKE
A LOOK HERE.

05:12.083 --> 05:14.250
(ultrasound whooshing)

05:14.291 --> 05:17.458
IS MY BABY OKAY?
SHE'S THE APPROPRIATE SIZE
FOR HER DATES.

05:17.500 --> 05:19.041
SHE?

05:19.083 --> 05:20.709
IT'S A GIRL?

05:20.750 --> 05:22.500
OH, Y-YES.
I'M SORRY. I--

05:22.542 --> 05:26.500
I'D APPRECIATE IT IF YOU COULD
MAKE IT AS QUICK AS POSSIBLE.

05:26.542 --> 05:28.709
I'D LIKE TO TAKE
MY DAUGHTER HOME.

05:28.750 --> 05:31.709
OKAY.

05:31.750 --> 05:33.083
WEIRD HOW?

05:33.125 --> 05:35.709
I DON'T KNOW. JUST WEIRD.
YOU'LL SEE.

05:35.750 --> 05:37.333
HI, I'M DR. BENNETT.

05:37.375 --> 05:38.959
I'M A CARDIOTHORACIC
SPECIALIST.

05:39.000 --> 05:41.333
I'D LIKE TO SPEAK WITH YOU
ABOUT YOUR SCANS.

05:41.375 --> 05:44.208
UH, IF YOU'D LIKE, YOUR FATHER
CAN WAIT IN THE LOUNGE.

05:44.250 --> 05:47.000
I'M FINE HERE.
OKAY. WELL...

05:47.041 --> 05:49.000
UH, WHAT YOU HAVE
IS AN AORTIC ANEURYSM.

05:49.041 --> 05:51.375
UH, IT'S AN ABNORMAL WIDENING

05:51.417 --> 05:53.834
OF THE LARGE ARTERY
IN YOUR ABDOMEN.

05:53.875 --> 05:57.041
WE'RE GOING TO NEED
TO DO SURGERY.
WE'RE HOPING TO AVOID IT
UNTIL THE BABY'S FURTHER ALONG,

05:57.083 --> 06:00.041
BUT WE WILL NEED TO KEEP YOU
HERE UNDER OBSERVATION.

06:00.083 --> 06:03.041
HOW LONG?
I DON'T KNOW. UH, WE'VE ORDERED
SOME REPEAT ULTRASOUNDS.

06:03.083 --> 06:05.041
AND WE'RE GOING TO NEED
TO REVIEW

06:05.083 --> 06:08.750
YOUR FAMILY MEDICAL HISTORY--
MOTHER, FATHER, SIBLINGS.

06:08.792 --> 06:10.125
MY MOTHER'S DEAD.

06:10.166 --> 06:12.208
WHY DO YOU NEED ALL THAT?
IT'S STANDARD.

06:12.250 --> 06:14.959
A MEDICAL HISTORY HELPS POINT US
IN THE RIGHT DIRECTION

06:15.000 --> 06:16.959
WHEN WE'RE TRYING
TO EVALUATE A PROBLEM.

06:17.000 --> 06:18.750
YOU AND I CAN TALK FURTHER

06:18.792 --> 06:20.750
WHILE YOUR DAUGHTER'S
UNDERGOING THE TEST.

06:20.792 --> 06:24.208
NO, I'M GOING WITH HER.

06:24.250 --> 06:26.041
(clears throat)

06:30.041 --> 06:34.166
DIDN'T YOUR MOTHER TEACH YOU,
IT'S NOT POLITE TO STARE?

06:34.208 --> 06:35.291
GABRIEL...

06:35.333 --> 06:38.375
I KNOW YOU'RE UPSET
WITH THE WAY WE LEFT THINGS.

06:38.417 --> 06:40.041
(wheelchair motor whirs)

06:40.083 --> 06:41.583
BUT WILLIAM NEEDED ME.

06:41.625 --> 06:43.041
HEY. I GET IT.

06:43.083 --> 06:45.417
ANY WOMAN IN YOUR POSITION
WOULD'VE MADE THE SAME CHOICE.

06:45.458 --> 06:47.041
IN THIS CORNER--

06:47.083 --> 06:49.041
ANGRY, SARCASTIC GUY
IN A WHEELCHAIR,

06:49.083 --> 06:51.041
WHO,
OBVIOUSLY A DYNAMO IN BED,

06:51.083 --> 06:53.041
CAN'T EXACTLY
SWEEP YOU OFF YOUR FEET.

06:53.083 --> 06:55.041
AND IN THIS CORNER,
YOU GOT OLD MONEYBAGS,

06:55.083 --> 06:57.166
WHO, IF YOU MARRY REAL QUICK,
WELL, LET'S JUST SAY,

06:57.208 --> 06:59.166
YOU'D MAKE FOR
AN EXTREMELY ATTRACTIVE,

06:59.208 --> 07:02.625
NOT TO MENTION
WEALTHY WIDOW.

07:05.583 --> 07:08.667
I WANT YOU TO TRY
THE A.L.S. PROTOCOL ON WILLIAM.

07:08.709 --> 07:11.041
THE ONE THAT STILL NEEDS
F.D.A. APPROVAL?

07:11.083 --> 07:14.125
THE ONE THAT WOULD BE COMPLETELY
DELEGITIMIZED IF WE USE IT?

07:14.166 --> 07:16.917
YES. WILL YOU DO IT?

07:16.959 --> 07:18.917
WOW. AMAZING.

07:18.959 --> 07:21.083
LITTLE MISS MORAL COMPASS

07:21.125 --> 07:24.083
IS SUDDENLY WILLING TO BLOW OFF
EVERYTHING SHE BELIEVES IN.

07:24.125 --> 07:28.041
GABRIEL... I'M ASKING YOU
TO THINK ABOUT IT.

07:28.083 --> 07:30.041
OKAY?

07:30.083 --> 07:31.834
JUST THINK ABOUT IT.

07:31.875 --> 07:33.834
(scoffs)

07:33.875 --> 07:35.583
HEY.

07:35.625 --> 07:39.041
SO, UH, BASED ON KIM'S
REPEAT SCAN,

07:39.083 --> 07:41.041
I RECOMMEND SURGERY NOW.

07:41.083 --> 07:43.041
OH, BUT THE FETUS
IS ONLY 30 WEEKS.

07:43.083 --> 07:44.583
IT'S TOO RISKY.

07:44.625 --> 07:47.792
YEAH, WELL, BLOWING
THE ANEURYSM COULD BE RISKIER.

07:47.834 --> 07:49.792
KIM TESTED POSITIVE
FOR THE GENE

07:49.834 --> 07:51.917
ASSOCIATED
WITH FIBRILLIN DISEASE?
YEAH, IT EXPLAINS
THE ANEURYSM.

07:51.959 --> 07:53.917
BUT IT'S
AN AUTOSOMAL DOMINANT DISEASE.

07:53.959 --> 07:56.667
I MEAN, IT'S INHERITED FROM
THE FATHER. IS SHE ADOPTED?

07:56.709 --> 08:00.083
WELL, GEORGE NEVER MENTIONED IT
IN HIS FAMILY HISTORY.

08:00.125 --> 08:01.667
HE DOESN'T HAVE THE DISEASE.

08:01.709 --> 08:04.041
HE'S NOT HER FATHER.
HE CAN'T BE.

08:04.083 --> 08:05.792
WELL, THEN WHO IS HE?

08:07.750 --> 08:10.500
(scanner thumping)

08:10.542 --> 08:12.709
SHE SAYS SHE FEELS GOD,

08:12.750 --> 08:14.500
AND IT CHANGED HER.

08:14.542 --> 08:16.083
JUST LIKE THAT,
SHE CHANGED?

08:16.125 --> 08:17.709
JUST LIKE THAT.

08:17.750 --> 08:19.083
PEOPLE DON'T CHANGE.

08:19.125 --> 08:20.750
OF COURSE THEY DO.

08:20.792 --> 08:22.750
THEY MODIFY. THEY ADJUST.

08:22.792 --> 08:25.333
BUT UNDERNEATH,
WE ARE WHO WE ARE.

08:25.375 --> 08:27.375
THAT'S NOT TRUE.

08:27.417 --> 08:29.709
I-I KNOW IT'S NOT TRUE.

08:29.750 --> 08:31.709
MY ENTIRE CAREER IS BASED ON

08:31.750 --> 08:33.750
HELPING PEOPLE
BECOME WHO THEY CAN BE.

08:33.792 --> 08:36.208
PEOPLE DO CHANGE.
I'VE SEEN IT.

08:36.250 --> 08:40.041
PEOPLE JUST GET BETTER
AT COVERING UP THEIR FLAWS.

08:40.083 --> 08:41.166
THERE.

08:41.208 --> 08:42.875
WHAT IS THAT?

08:42.917 --> 08:46.041
(beeping)
THAT... IS CLAIRE'S GOD.

08:54.500 --> 08:57.041
DON'T YOU GUYS HAVE
YOUR OWN CEREAL DOWNSTAIRS?

08:57.083 --> 08:59.041
(mouth full)
NAOMI DOESN'T LET US

08:59.083 --> 09:02.250
BUY THE KIND
WITH MARSHMALLOWS IN IT.

09:02.291 --> 09:04.875
HEY. HOW DO YOU GET
SOMEONE TO TALK TO YOU

09:04.917 --> 09:06.333
THAT WON'T TALK TO YOU?

09:06.375 --> 09:08.959
(normal voice) CHARLOTTE?
UH, NO, NOT THIS TIME.

09:09.000 --> 09:10.834
ACTUALLY, WE'RE DOING OKAY.
IT'S VIOLET.

09:10.875 --> 09:13.125
SHE'S BEING...
I DON'T KNOW, MEAN TO ME.

09:13.166 --> 09:16.166
SHE'S BEING MEAN TO ME,
AND SHE'S NEVER MEAN TO ME.

09:16.208 --> 09:18.041
AND I SAID I WAS SORRY.

09:18.083 --> 09:20.041
WELL, JUST, UH,
KEEP ON KEEPING ON.

09:20.083 --> 09:22.041
IS THAT THE BEST YOU CAN DO?

09:22.083 --> 09:25.291
'CAUSE I CAN GET THAT
FROM A BUMPER STICKER.
SHE'S HURT, COOPER.

09:25.333 --> 09:27.291
YOU CAN'T EXPECT HER
TO COME AROUND

09:27.333 --> 09:29.291
AS SOON
AS YOU APOLOGIZE TO HER.

09:29.333 --> 09:32.291
BECAUSE EVEN IF SHE UNDERSTANDS
YOUR EXPLANATION INTELLECTUALLY,

09:32.333 --> 09:35.041
SHE, UH, STILL HAS TO
ACCEPT IT... EMOTIONALLY.

09:35.083 --> 09:36.667
AND THAT TAKES TIME.

09:36.709 --> 09:39.583
SO KEEP ON KEEPIN' ON.

09:39.625 --> 09:41.375
EXACTLY.

09:41.417 --> 09:43.500
OKAY.

09:43.542 --> 09:46.041
HEY, UH, YOU WANT TO HEAR
SOMETHING PRETTY COOL,

09:46.083 --> 09:48.041
SOMETHING I HAVEN'T TOLD
ANYBODY ELSE?

09:48.083 --> 09:50.959
(lowered voice) I GOT INTO
U.C.L.A. MEDICAL SCHOOL.

09:51.000 --> 09:52.959
OH, MY GOD!
(normal voice)
OH, OH, OH, OKAY.

09:53.000 --> 09:55.041
THAT'S FANTASTIC.
CONGRATULATIONS.

09:55.083 --> 09:58.041
YEAH, I HAVE NO IDEA
HOW I'D PAY FOR IT, BUT--

09:58.083 --> 10:00.333
HEY.
OH, I'M SORRY I'M LATE.

10:00.375 --> 10:02.542
I HOPE I DIDN'T MISS
ALL THE FUN.

10:02.583 --> 10:04.959
NO, WE'RE
JUST GETTING STARTED.
HEY, MOM.

10:05.041 --> 10:07.291
HEY. THANKS FOR
HAVING ME HERE, HON.

10:07.333 --> 10:10.041
WOW. THREE WEEKS TO GO.
YEAH.
EVERYTHING LOOKS GREAT.

10:10.083 --> 10:12.458
HEART RATE IS STRONG.
YEAH?

10:12.500 --> 10:15.125
YEAH.
OH, I REMEMBER
MY LAST MONTH WITH YOU.

10:15.166 --> 10:17.125
I WAS SO NERVOUS,
KEPT LOOKING UP

10:17.166 --> 10:19.125
EVERY POSSIBLE OBSTETRIC
COMPLICATION IN THE BOOK.

10:19.166 --> 10:21.583
I WAS DRIVING YOUR DAD CRAZY.
(laughs)
(chuckles)

10:21.625 --> 10:24.458
IT CAN BE A LITTLE SCARY,
YOU KNOW?

10:24.500 --> 10:26.542
SO DO YOU HAVE
ANY QUESTIONS?

10:26.583 --> 10:28.750
I'M FINE.
YOU HAVE A PLAN?

10:28.792 --> 10:31.041
I'VE GOT IT ALL WORKED OUT--
TOTALLY NATURAL BIRTH...

10:31.083 --> 10:33.041
DELL'S DOING
THE DELIVERY HERE.
UH-HUH.

10:33.083 --> 10:35.458
I DO MY SQUATTING EXERCISES
IN THE MORNING,

10:35.500 --> 10:37.667
MY RELAXATION TECHNIQUES
IN THE AFTERNOON.

10:37.709 --> 10:39.667
THAT'S SO I WON'T NEED
AN EPIDURAL.

10:39.709 --> 10:41.250
UM, MY BAG IS PACKED,

10:41.291 --> 10:44.250
AND DINK MADE A MIX CD
FOR MY BIRTHING MUSIC.

10:44.291 --> 10:46.041
I'M SO READY.

10:46.083 --> 10:47.667
(laughs) WOW.

10:47.709 --> 10:50.041
WOW. YOU'VE JUST--
YOU'VE THOUGHT OF EVERYTHING.

10:50.083 --> 10:52.041
YOU DON'T HAVE TO WORRY
ABOUT ME, MOM.

10:52.083 --> 10:55.041
YOU NOT BEING AROUND
ACTUALLY HELPED.

10:55.083 --> 10:57.041
IT GAVE ME A CHANCE
TO GROW UP,

10:57.083 --> 11:00.000
FIGURE THINGS OUT
ON MY OWN.

11:01.792 --> 11:04.208
THANKS FOR DOING
THE CONSULT, SHELDON.

11:04.250 --> 11:06.583
ORDINARILY, I'D ASK VIOLET,
BUT THINGS HAVE BEEN

11:06.625 --> 11:09.041
A LITTLE WEIRD
SINCE THE TRI--
(emergency bell rings)

11:09.083 --> 11:10.417
SHELDON?

11:10.458 --> 11:12.417
I KNOW, STOPPING ELEVATORS
IS YOUR THING,

11:12.458 --> 11:14.417
BUT TODAY, I... (laughs)

11:14.458 --> 11:16.834
I NEED TO CHANGE THINGS UP
A LITTLE.

11:16.875 --> 11:19.125
WAIT. YOU NEED HELP...
FROM ME?

11:19.166 --> 11:21.417
SHELDON, YOU SENT ME A BILL
LAST TIME.

11:21.458 --> 11:24.417
WHEN I ASKED FOR
ELEVATOR ADVICE, YOU CHARGED ME.

11:24.458 --> 11:27.625
ALL RIGHT. WELL, I'M GONNA SEND
YOU A BILL, AND I'M EXPENSIVE.

11:27.667 --> 11:29.208
I HAVE MANY
BOARD CERTIFICATIONS.

11:29.250 --> 11:31.208
ONLY EIGHT PEOPLE IN THE WORLD
DO WHAT I DO.

11:31.250 --> 11:34.000
I CAN GIVE YOU A PAP SMEAR,
OPERATE ON YOUR UTERUS

11:34.041 --> 11:37.667
AND PERFORM SURGERY ON YOUR BABY
BEFORE AND AFTER HE'S BORN.

11:37.709 --> 11:40.041
ARE YOU GONNA LISTEN TO ME
OR NOT?

11:40.083 --> 11:41.417
ALL RIGHT. SPILL IT.

11:41.458 --> 11:44.041
IT'S ABOUT CHARLOTTE.
I'VE BEEN GIVING HER ADVICE

11:44.083 --> 11:47.667
ON HOW TO GET BACK TOGETHER
WITH COOPER, BUT THE THING IS,

11:47.709 --> 11:51.000
I THINK ABOUT HER, ADDISON.

11:51.041 --> 11:53.375
WHEN SHE'S NOT AROUND, I THINK
ABOUT THE WAY SHE SMILES,

11:53.417 --> 11:55.041
THE WAY SHE LOOKS AT ME.
I-I...

11:55.083 --> 11:58.041
MY GOD, I SPEND HALF MY DAY
COMING UP WITH LAME REASONS

11:58.083 --> 12:00.250
TO GO UP AND VISIT HER.

12:00.291 --> 12:03.208
D-DO YOU KNOW HOW MANY TIMES
I'VE BORROWED STAMPS FROM HER?

12:03.250 --> 12:06.917
I DON'T EVEN USE STAMPS.
I PAY MY BILLS ELECTRONICALLY.

12:06.959 --> 12:09.625
LISTEN TO ME, SHELDON.

12:09.667 --> 12:11.625
YOU WANT HER? GO GET HER.

12:11.667 --> 12:13.625
YOU HAVE TO TRY.
IF NOT, YOU'RE GONNA SPEND

12:13.667 --> 12:16.166
THE REST OF YOUR LIFE
KICKING YOURSELF

12:16.208 --> 12:20.208
AND WONDERING WHY YOU DIDN'T
MAN UP AND GO FOR IT.

12:20.250 --> 12:23.041
THANK YOU.

12:23.083 --> 12:25.083
(emergency bell rings,
motor starts)

12:25.125 --> 12:28.500
DO YOU HAVE
THE TEST RESULTS?

12:28.542 --> 12:31.500
CAN WE GO HOME NOW?
ACTUALLY, THE RESULTS
WERE INCONCLUSIVE.

12:31.542 --> 12:35.041
WE'RE GONNA NEED HER
FOR ONE MORE TEST.

12:35.083 --> 12:37.417
YOU CAN STAY HERE.
WHY? I WANT TO BE WITH HER.

12:37.458 --> 12:39.750
WE NEED HER FOR RADIOLOGY,
SOME X-RAYS.

12:39.792 --> 12:41.750
YOU'RE NOT ALLOWED
IN THE ROOM.

12:41.792 --> 12:43.750
IT'S ALL RIGHT.
SHE'LL BE RIGHT BACK.

12:43.792 --> 12:47.083
I'LL BE WAITING
FOR YOU HERE, KIM.

12:47.125 --> 12:48.750
APPRECIATE IT.

12:48.792 --> 12:50.750
(woman speaks indistinctly
over p.a.)

12:50.792 --> 12:53.333
GOD IS IN A BRAIN TUMOR?

12:53.375 --> 12:54.458
(laughs)

12:54.500 --> 12:57.083
I'M SORRY.
THAT SOUNDS RIDICULOUS.

12:57.125 --> 12:59.667
WELL, IT'S ACTUALLY
A WELL-KNOWN PHENOMENA.

12:59.709 --> 13:01.125
THE TEMPORAL LOBE

13:01.166 --> 13:03.834
CONTAINS THE EMOTIONAL ENGINE
OF OUR BRAINS.

13:03.875 --> 13:05.834
IT'S THE CENTER
OF ALL OF OUR FEELINGS.

13:05.875 --> 13:08.250
SO ANYTHING--RAGE, LUST,
ANGER, PASSION, BLISS--

13:08.291 --> 13:10.875
ANYTHING THAT STIMULATES
THAT PART OF THE BRAIN

13:10.917 --> 13:12.500
CAN ELICIT THOSE FEELINGS.

13:12.542 --> 13:14.750
BUT THEY'RE NOT REAL.

13:14.792 --> 13:16.750
THEY'RE JUST MISDIRECTED
NEURAL IMPULSES.

13:16.792 --> 13:19.125
THEY'RE...
RANDOM SHORT CIRCUITS.

13:19.166 --> 13:21.041
YOU'RE WRONG.

13:21.083 --> 13:23.041
THEY ARE REAL.

13:23.083 --> 13:26.709
I CAN FEEL IT.
IT'S HAPPINESS.

13:26.750 --> 13:29.041
I'VE NEVER FELT IT BEFORE,
BUT... (laughs)

13:29.083 --> 13:32.000
IT'S LIKE I-I HAD THIS GIANT
WEIGHT ON MY SHOULDERS

13:32.041 --> 13:34.041
AND--AND NOW
THE WEIGHT IS LIFTED.

13:34.083 --> 13:36.000
THAT DOESN'T JUST HAPPEN,
THAT'S NOT JUST...

13:36.041 --> 13:37.792
CHEMICAL REACTIONS
IN MY BRAIN.

13:37.834 --> 13:39.291
AND YOU KNOW WHAT?

13:39.333 --> 13:42.333
IF IT TAKES A MAGIC BULLET
IN MY HEAD TO DO GOD'S WORK,

13:42.375 --> 13:44.750
THEN THAT'S HIS PLAN.

13:46.667 --> 13:50.041
IT'S A SLOW-GROWING TUMOR.

13:50.083 --> 13:52.500
WITH SURGERY, YOUR CHANCE
OF RECOVERY IS EXCELLENT.

13:52.542 --> 13:54.000
BUT WITHOUT IT...

13:56.750 --> 14:00.417
WHAT, YOU'RE SAYING THIS TUMOR'S
GONNA KILL MY WIFE?

14:03.792 --> 14:06.000
WITHOUT THE SURGERY,
YOU WILL DIE.

14:11.083 --> 14:13.041
I SPENT THREE YEARS

14:13.083 --> 14:15.041
IN INTENSIVE THERAPY
WITH DR. TURNER,

14:15.083 --> 14:18.458
AND I DIDN'T HAVE
A HAPPY BONE IN MY BODY.

14:18.500 --> 14:22.667
NOW I'VE FOUND GOD.
HE'S IN ME.

14:22.709 --> 14:26.291
IF DYING IS GOD'S PLAN,
THEN SO BE IT.

14:30.375 --> 14:32.959
I THOUGHT WE WERE GOING
TO RADIOLOGY.
UH, WE ARE.

14:33.000 --> 14:35.959
I JUST WANTED YOU TO CONSULT
WITH ONE MORE DOCTOR, KIM,

14:36.000 --> 14:37.333
BEFORE WE DO YOUR TEST.

14:37.375 --> 14:39.250
(woman speaks indistinctly
over p.a.)

14:39.291 --> 14:41.917
HI, KIM.
I'M DR. WALLACE.

14:45.500 --> 14:46.834
NOTHING?

14:46.875 --> 14:48.917
NOTHING? DID YOU--DID YOU
CHECK WITH N.I.H.?

14:48.959 --> 14:52.166
YEAH, I KNOW, I KNOW.
I KNEW IT WAS A LONG SHOT.

14:52.208 --> 14:54.083
THANK YOU FOR TRYING,
DR. KLEIN.

14:54.125 --> 14:55.709
OKAY.

14:55.750 --> 14:57.208
(receiver clatters)

15:01.291 --> 15:03.250
WHAT DO I HAVE TO DO,
GABRIEL?

15:03.291 --> 15:06.417
DO I HAVE TO BEG?
OKAY, I WILL BEG.

15:06.458 --> 15:08.500
WHAT YOU'RE ASKING
IS UNETHICAL AND ILLEGAL.

15:08.542 --> 15:11.208
THE PROTOCOL IS NOT APPROVED.

15:11.250 --> 15:13.291
IF I GIVE IT TO WILLIAM,
IT WILL NEVER BE.

15:13.333 --> 15:15.583
AND I AM STILL ASKING.

15:15.625 --> 15:18.041
NO.

15:18.083 --> 15:20.834
IF YOU DON'T HELP HIM,
HE IS GOING TO DIE.

15:25.125 --> 15:28.333
WELL, THEN I GUESS
HE'S GOING TO DIE.

15:37.333 --> 15:39.125
SHE'S RATIONAL AND ORIENTED.

15:39.166 --> 15:41.041
THERE'S NO EVIDENCE
OF DELUSIONAL THINKING.

15:41.083 --> 15:42.917
SHE'S ENTIRELY CAPABLE

15:42.959 --> 15:45.917
OF MAKING DECISIONS
ABOUT HER OWN TREATMENT, SO--
SHE CAN'T DECIDE.

15:45.959 --> 15:48.500
SHE THINKS SHE HAS
A PERSONAL PIPELINE TO GOD.

15:48.542 --> 15:51.041
THIS WOMAN WAS MISERABLE
HER ENTIRE LIFE UNTIL NOW.

15:51.083 --> 15:53.041
AND YOU ARE TELLING HER
TO ACCEPT A TREATMENT

15:53.083 --> 15:55.041
THAT WOULD BRING
ALL THAT PAIN BACK,

15:55.083 --> 15:57.667
TO JUST LIVE WITH IT.

15:57.709 --> 15:59.917
I-I MAY NOT AGREE
WITH HER DECISION,

15:59.959 --> 16:01.959
BUT I CERTAINLY UNDERSTAND
HER REFUSAL

16:02.000 --> 16:04.250
TO LET YOU DO THAT TO HER.

16:04.291 --> 16:06.291
WHY WOULD ANYONE CHOOSE
TO FEEL WORSE?

16:06.333 --> 16:09.458
BECAUSE WITHOUT THE SURGERY,
SHE WILL DIE.

16:09.500 --> 16:11.041
AND CLAIRE UNDERSTANDS THAT.

16:11.083 --> 16:13.083
SHE BELIEVES
IT'S PART OF GOD'S PLAN.

16:13.125 --> 16:16.500
IF GOD
IS NOT GONNA DO HIS JOB,

16:16.542 --> 16:21.041
I GUESS I'LL HAVE TO DO IT
FOR HIM.

16:21.083 --> 16:23.000
SO YOU DON'T REMEMBER
YOUR MOTHER AT ALL?

16:23.041 --> 16:24.041
NO.

16:24.083 --> 16:26.041
WELL, HOW OLD WERE YOU
WHEN SHE DIED?

16:26.083 --> 16:28.834
I'M NOT SURE.

16:30.583 --> 16:32.750
YOU KEEP LOOKING AT THE DOOR.

16:32.792 --> 16:35.041
ARE YOU AFRAID
YOUR FATHER'S GONNA COME IN?

16:35.083 --> 16:37.458
OR HOPING HE'LL COME IN?

16:39.583 --> 16:41.542
DO YOU HAVE PLANS
FOR YOUR FUTURE?

16:41.583 --> 16:45.041
DO YOU WANT
TO GO TO COLLEGE OR...

16:45.083 --> 16:47.542
MY DAD DOESN'T THINK
I NEED IT.

16:47.583 --> 16:50.750
WELL, THE TWO OF YOU,
YOU'RE VERY CLOSE.

16:50.792 --> 16:54.750
WE HAVE
A SPECIAL RELATIONSHIP.

16:56.375 --> 16:58.333
HOW SO?

16:58.375 --> 17:01.625
WHEN'S MY DAD GONNA BE BACK?

17:01.667 --> 17:04.667
SOON.

17:04.709 --> 17:06.583
KIM,
THIS ABNORMALITY YOU HAVE,

17:06.625 --> 17:09.166
IT'S A CONDITION
YOU INHERIT FROM A FATHER--

17:09.208 --> 17:12.166
ONLY FROM A FATHER--
AND GEORGE DOESN'T HAVE IT.

17:12.208 --> 17:14.166
MY DAD SAYS
DOCTORS DON'T KNOW

17:14.208 --> 17:17.959
WHAT THEY'RE TALKING ABOUT
HALF THE TIME.

17:18.000 --> 17:19.458
WELL, YOUR FATHER...

17:19.500 --> 17:21.458
HE SEEMS TO KNOW EVERYTHING.

17:21.500 --> 17:24.792
OF COURSE HE DOES.

17:24.834 --> 17:26.834
HE'S MY DAD.

17:28.500 --> 17:31.041
HER ANSWERS FELT REHEARSED,
YOU KNOW, AND PLANNED.

17:31.083 --> 17:33.000
AND SHE'S BEEN
EXTREMELY ISOLATED.

17:33.041 --> 17:35.000
SHE DOESN'T WATCH TV
OR USE THE INTERNET.

17:35.041 --> 17:37.875
SHE CAN'T EVEN REMEMBER
THE LAST TIME SHE LEFT THE FARM.

17:37.917 --> 17:40.041
I THINK WE SHOULD CALL
THE POLICE.

17:40.083 --> 17:42.500
THE POLICE?
I'M NOT 100% SURE, BUT I THINK
WE MAY BE WITNESSING

17:42.542 --> 17:44.500
A KIDNAPPED GIRL
AND HER ABDUCTOR.

17:44.542 --> 17:46.458
(Addison) WHAT?

17:48.083 --> 17:50.208
WE'RE LEAVING.

17:51.959 --> 17:53.458
KIM, GET OUT OF BED.

17:53.500 --> 17:55.250
GET YOUR STUFF.
WE'RE GOING HOME.

17:55.291 --> 17:57.875
(Addison) NO, GEORGE.
YOU CAN'T LEAVE.
NO, GEORGE. WHOA.

17:57.917 --> 18:00.959
THIS IS MY FAMILY,
AND WE ARE LEAVING.
GEORGE. G-GEORGE.

18:01.000 --> 18:03.875
ALL RIGHT. NO. GEORGE.
YOU'RE NOT GOING ANYWHERE.
WHAT ARE YOU DOING?!

18:03.917 --> 18:06.083
(Addison)
GET BACK INTO BED, KIM. KIM.
LET HIM GO!

18:06.125 --> 18:08.709
KIM!
YES, I NEED SECURITY.
3-0-1 EAST.

18:08.750 --> 18:10.917
YOU'RE HURTING MY FATHER.
I LOVE YOU.

18:10.959 --> 18:12.834
PLEASE.
YOU'RE GOING TO HURT HIM.
WE'RE FAMILY.

18:12.875 --> 18:15.250
YOU HAVE TO GET BACK INTO BED.
SAM! SAM, A LITTLE HELP HERE.

18:15.291 --> 18:17.041
SHE'S UNCONSCIOUS.
(Sam) OKAY.

18:17.083 --> 18:21.667
SHE'S BOTTOMING OUT.
CALL THE O.R. WE GOT
A TRIPLE-A THAT'S BLEEDING OUT.

18:21.709 --> 18:23.458
OKAY. EASY.

18:23.500 --> 18:25.000
(footsteps approach)

18:29.709 --> 18:32.041
ARE WE GONNA
TALK ABOUT THIS?

18:32.083 --> 18:34.125
(exhales)

18:34.166 --> 18:36.083
HUH.

18:39.667 --> 18:42.875
I GUESS WE'RE NOT
GONNA TALK ABOUT THIS.

18:42.917 --> 18:45.917
(Sarah Jaffe's "Clementine"
playing)

18:49.333 --> 18:51.041
THERE'S GOTTA BE
SOMETHING ELSE.

18:51.083 --> 18:55.375
NAOMI...
WE'VE BEEN THROUGH THIS.

18:55.417 --> 18:58.959
WHATEVER TIME I HAVE LEFT,
I WANT TO SPEND IT WITH YOU...

18:59.000 --> 19:00.041
I...

19:00.083 --> 19:02.500
ENJOYING EACH OTHER...

19:02.542 --> 19:06.542
NOT CHASING
SOME IMPOSSIBLE CURE.

19:06.583 --> 19:08.041
THERE'S NOTHING LEFT TO DO.

19:08.083 --> 19:11.041
♪ NOW I'M FEELING DIFFERENT ♪

19:11.083 --> 19:12.458
(speaking indistinctly)

19:12.500 --> 19:14.458
YOU CAN'T LEAVE.

19:14.500 --> 19:16.959
WHAT?
I'VE MADE MY DECISION.

19:17.000 --> 19:18.959
IRWIN AND I ARE GOING HOME.

19:19.000 --> 19:21.083
BUT YOU--
PLEASE DON'T TRY
TO CONVINCE ME.

19:21.125 --> 19:22.709
I'M HAPPY.

19:22.750 --> 19:25.333
I'M FINALLY HAPPY,
AND I DON'T WANNA GO BACK.

19:25.375 --> 19:27.542
I UNDERSTAND HOW YOU FEEL.

19:27.583 --> 19:29.125
NO, YOU COULDN'T POSSIBLY.

19:29.166 --> 19:33.083
MY FATHER WAS MURDERED.

19:33.125 --> 19:36.041
MY BROTHER AND I WERE THERE
WHEN IT HAPPENED.

19:36.083 --> 19:38.500
I-I WAS JUST A KID
AT THE TIME. I...

19:38.542 --> 19:42.041
BUT THE BOTTOM FELL OUT...
OF MY WHOLE WORLD.

19:42.083 --> 19:43.542
I-I WAS...

19:43.583 --> 19:45.542
♪ ...TIME ♪

19:45.583 --> 19:48.041
THERE WAS A DARK PLACE,
AND I WAS IN IT.

19:48.083 --> 19:50.208
UNTIL ONE DAY, THIS FRIEND

19:50.250 --> 19:51.834
GAVE ME A PILL.

19:51.875 --> 19:53.583
AND... I TOOK IT,

19:53.625 --> 19:56.542
AND ALL OF A SUDDEN...

19:56.583 --> 19:58.041
I FELT OKAY,

19:58.083 --> 20:00.041
BETTER THAN OKAY.

20:00.083 --> 20:02.166
I FELT GOOD.

20:02.208 --> 20:04.166
AND SO I KEPT TAKING THEM.

20:04.208 --> 20:08.208
AND I FELT...

20:08.250 --> 20:10.166
GREAT.

20:10.208 --> 20:12.792
AND WHEN PEOPLE WOULD TRY
TO GET ME TO STOP

20:12.834 --> 20:15.166
AND TELL ME THAT IT WASN'T REAL,
I WOULD JUST LAUGH,

20:15.208 --> 20:17.166
BECAUSE IT WAS REAL.

20:17.208 --> 20:19.208
HOW I FELT--IT WAS BETTER.

20:19.250 --> 20:21.458
IT WAS BETTER...

20:21.500 --> 20:23.208
THAN BEING MISERABLE.

20:23.250 --> 20:25.041
BUT IT ALMOST KILLED ME.

20:25.083 --> 20:27.041
I WAS DEAD FOR THREE MINUTES.

20:27.083 --> 20:30.375
AND LET ME TELL YOU, WHEN YOU
ARE LYING ON A STRETCHER,

20:30.417 --> 20:33.000
GASPING FOR WHAT YOU THINK
ARE YOUR LAST BREATHS,

20:33.041 --> 20:36.041
YOU DON'T THINK THAT DYING HAPPY
IS BETTER THAN LIVING SAD.

20:36.083 --> 20:39.375
DYING... SUCKS.

20:39.417 --> 20:41.709
♪ 50 CRYING ALL THE TIMES ♪

20:41.750 --> 20:43.417
IT HURTS...

20:43.458 --> 20:46.041
IN A WAY
THAT I CAN'T DESCRIBE TO YOU.

20:46.083 --> 20:47.625
AND, NO...

20:47.667 --> 20:50.250
I DON'T BELIEVE
THAT PEOPLE CAN CHANGE.

20:50.291 --> 20:52.250
I DON'T BELIEVE
THAT YOU'LL CHANGE.

20:52.291 --> 20:54.458
BUT MAYBE I'M WRONG.

20:54.500 --> 20:57.458
AND, HELL, MAYBE YOU WILL
WAKE UP FROM THAT SURGERY

20:57.500 --> 20:59.041
AND YOU WILL BE HAPPY.

20:59.083 --> 21:02.041
BUT IF YOU'RE DEAD,
IF YOU ARE ROTTING IN THE GROUND

21:02.083 --> 21:04.500
FROM SOME TUMOR
THAT ATE YOUR BRAIN,

21:04.542 --> 21:06.500
YOU DON'T GET A CHANCE
TO FIND THAT OUT.

21:06.542 --> 21:10.875
♪ IS IT GONE? IS IT GONE?
OR IS IT FLOATING... ♪

21:10.917 --> 21:12.875
AND ONE MORE THING,
AND THEN I WILL GO.

21:12.917 --> 21:16.041
I'M... (inhales deeply)
I'M NOT A RELIGIOUS PERSON.

21:16.083 --> 21:19.917
I... DON'T BELIEVE IN GOD.

21:19.959 --> 21:23.041
BUT IF I DID...

21:23.083 --> 21:26.041
I WOULDN'T BELIEVE IN A GOD
THAT WANTED YOU TO DIE

21:26.083 --> 21:29.709
THE HORRIBLE, PAINFUL DEATH
THAT YOU WILL EXPERIENCE

21:29.750 --> 21:33.166
FROM A GIANT TUMOR THAT WILL
TAKE AWAY YOUR ABILITY TO SPEAK

21:33.208 --> 21:37.166
AND SEE AND GO TO THE BATHROOM
AND BREATHE ON YOUR OWN.

21:37.208 --> 21:39.041
THAT CAN'T BE GOD.

21:39.083 --> 21:41.750
♪ ...A LITTLE MORE DELICATE ♪

21:46.125 --> 21:47.291
OKAY.

21:47.333 --> 21:49.041
WAIT A MINUTE.

21:49.083 --> 21:50.041
CLAIRE.

21:50.083 --> 21:51.875
NO, NO,
IT'S TOO DANGEROUS...

21:51.917 --> 21:53.750
AND GOD IS TELLING YOU--

21:53.792 --> 21:55.917
SEE, MAYBE SHE'S RIGHT.

21:55.959 --> 21:58.709
MAYBE THIS IS WHAT GOD WANTS.

21:58.750 --> 22:00.166
ALL RIGHT?

22:00.208 --> 22:02.083
I'LL DO IT.
I'LL DO THE SURGERY.

22:02.125 --> 22:05.125
♪♪♪

22:11.000 --> 22:12.834
(Jason Walker)
♪ OH, NO, WHERE DID ALL... ♪

22:12.875 --> 22:14.750
WE'RE LOSING HER, SAM.
ALL RIGHT.

22:14.792 --> 22:17.834
HANG ANOTHER 4 UNITS
ON THE INFUSER. SUCTION.

22:17.875 --> 22:20.792
SHE'S BLEEDING OUT.
CROSS-CLAMP THE AORTA.
THERE'S TOO MUCH BLOOD
IN THE FIELD.

22:20.834 --> 22:22.625
I CAN'T SEE A THING.

22:22.667 --> 22:25.041
GIVE ME YOUR HAND.
GIVE ME YOUR HAND.

22:25.083 --> 22:26.625
♪ THAT WAS HANDED TO... ♪

22:26.667 --> 22:29.834
OKAY, YOU FEEL THAT?
RIGHT THERE. YOU FEEL IT?
NO.

22:29.875 --> 22:31.625
MOVE CLOSER.

22:31.667 --> 22:34.041
♪ ...MAKE SENSE ♪

22:34.083 --> 22:35.542
(monitor beeping erratically)

22:35.583 --> 22:38.166
OKAY, NOW PUSH DOWN.

22:38.208 --> 22:40.834
RIGHT THERE. DON'T STOP.

22:40.875 --> 22:44.875
♪ IS TRYING TO FIND A WAY
TO LET YOU KNOW ♪

22:44.917 --> 22:46.792
OKAY, MORE SUCTION.

22:46.834 --> 22:48.750
(beeping continues)

22:48.792 --> 22:50.959
ALL RIGHT.

22:51.000 --> 22:53.792
2 CENTIMETERS TO THE LEFT.

22:53.834 --> 22:55.166
GOT IT.

22:55.208 --> 22:57.458
THERE WE GO.
DEBAKEY CLAMP.

22:57.500 --> 23:01.333
♪ CAN'T IT JUST BE OVER? ♪

23:01.375 --> 23:04.375
(monitor beeping rhythmically)
PRESSURE'S COMING UP.

23:04.417 --> 23:06.667
♪ CRY UNTIL IT'S ALL GONE ♪

23:06.709 --> 23:09.041
OKAY.
(clears throat)

23:09.083 --> 23:10.917
OH, IT'S OKAY.

23:10.959 --> 23:12.417
♪ TIME FOR US TO... ♪

23:12.458 --> 23:14.417
SO CLAIRE IS IN PRE-OP.

23:14.458 --> 23:16.417
SHE SAID I'D FIND YOU HERE.

23:16.458 --> 23:19.083
♪ I'M TIRED OF TRYING
TO FIND A REASON WHY ♪

23:19.125 --> 23:21.709
YOU KNOW, DR. SHEPHERD
IS AN EXCELLENT SURGEON.

23:21.750 --> 23:23.083
IT'LL BE OKAY.

23:23.125 --> 23:25.917
NO, IT WON'T.

23:25.959 --> 23:29.500
NO, YOU WERE THERE.
YOU WERE IN THERAPY WITH US.

23:29.542 --> 23:31.625
IT WAS HELL
LIVING WITH HER.

23:31.667 --> 23:34.500
♪ ...THINKING 'BOUT MY LIFE ♪

23:34.542 --> 23:36.291
YOU KNOW, SUDDENLY, I FIND

23:36.333 --> 23:38.500
THE WOMAN
I'VE ALWAYS DREAMED OF,

23:38.542 --> 23:41.625
AND IN A FEW HOURS,
SHE MIGHT BE GONE.

23:41.667 --> 23:43.667
I'M NOT SURE
I HAVE IT IN ME

23:43.709 --> 23:45.667
TO LOVE
THE OLD CLAIRE ANYMORE.

23:45.709 --> 23:47.667
SEE, I LOVE HER
THE WAY SHE IS NOW...

23:47.709 --> 23:51.083
(crying) WITH THAT DAMN TUMOR
IN HER HEAD.

23:51.125 --> 23:54.166
♪ ...YESTERDAY ♪

23:55.792 --> 23:57.917
♪ BUT THE HARDEST PART... ♪

23:57.959 --> 23:59.291
I DON'T KNOW

23:59.333 --> 24:02.125
WHAT'S GONNA HAPPEN
AFTER THE SURGERY.

24:02.166 --> 24:06.083
BUT WE'VE SEEN CLAIRE
FOR WHO SHE CAN BE.

24:06.125 --> 24:09.041
AND I DO BELIEVE
THE JOY SHE FEELS NOW

24:09.083 --> 24:13.291
COMES FROM A DEEPER PLACE
THAN A LESION IN HER HEAD.

24:13.333 --> 24:16.041
SOMEWHERE INSIDE OF HER...

24:16.083 --> 24:18.917
THAT PART MUST EXIST.

24:18.959 --> 24:22.542
DO YOU REALLY BELIEVE THAT?

24:22.583 --> 24:24.041
♪ AND WE'LL JUST CRY ♪

24:24.083 --> 24:27.583
♪ CRY, CRY
UNTIL IT'S ALL GONE ♪

24:27.625 --> 24:31.041
♪ BEEN HOLDING
ON FOR TOO LONG ♪

24:31.083 --> 24:34.041
YOU MAY BE SMART AND INSIGHTFUL
AND SOME KIND OF SUPER SHRINK,

24:34.083 --> 24:36.166
BUT I KNOW COOPER,
AND I SHOULDN'T HAVE LISTENED.
CHARLOTTE--

24:36.208 --> 24:38.583
HE IS WHO HE IS. HE'S FUNNY,
NEUROTIC IN THAT WAY

24:38.625 --> 24:40.583
MY MAMA WARNED ME
WOULDN'T BE CUTE AFTER A WHILE

24:40.625 --> 24:43.291
AND A FREAK BETWEEN THE SHEETS,
BUT HE'S NOT ANY MORE THAN THAT,

24:43.333 --> 24:45.291
AND HE ISN'T GONNA BE.

24:45.333 --> 24:47.291
♪ CRY ♪

24:47.333 --> 24:49.125
WELL, I WILL BE...

24:49.166 --> 24:50.834
MORE TO YOU.

24:50.875 --> 24:52.709
I... I WILL BE.

24:52.750 --> 24:54.709
YOU'RE RIGHT.
YOU SHOULD EXPECT MORE.

24:54.750 --> 24:57.709
AND FROM THE MAN IN YOUR LIFE,
YOU SHOULD EXPECT EVERYTHING--

24:57.750 --> 25:01.041
TRUST AND EMOTIONAL SUPPORT
AND INTELLECTUAL STIMULATION.

25:01.083 --> 25:03.083
AND YOU SHOULD EXPECT
THAT HE'LL BE THERE FOR YOU

25:03.125 --> 25:05.083
UNCONDITIONALLY,
NO MATTER WHAT YOU DO,

25:05.125 --> 25:07.083
NO MATTER
WHAT LIFE BRINGS YOU,

25:07.125 --> 25:09.208
AND--AND SEX, TOO--GREAT SEX--

25:09.250 --> 25:13.000
PLUS A GREAT RECIPE FOR HAGGIS.

25:13.041 --> 25:14.917
I MEAN,
YOU SHOULD GET EVERYTHING.

25:14.959 --> 25:16.291
I'LL GIVE YOU EVERYTHING,

25:16.333 --> 25:18.625
THE WHOLE PACKAGE, RIGHT DOWN
TO THE PICKET FENCE.

25:18.667 --> 25:21.041
I'LL GIVE IT TO YOU.
SHELDON WALLACE.

25:21.083 --> 25:24.417
I'M THROWING MY HAT
IN THE RING.

25:24.458 --> 25:27.875
HAVE DINNER WITH ME...
TONIGHT.

25:27.917 --> 25:29.875
♪ ...A REASON WHY ♪

25:29.917 --> 25:32.041
YOU WERE GREAT.
I WAS GREAT.

25:32.083 --> 25:33.458
YEAH, WE DID GOOD.

25:33.500 --> 25:35.458
GOOD?
WE SAVED TWO LIVES TODAY--

25:35.500 --> 25:37.458
TWO FOR THE PRICE OF ONE.

25:37.500 --> 25:40.041
I MEAN, HOW OFTEN
DO YOU GET TO SAY THAT?

25:40.083 --> 25:43.041
I MEAN, CAN YOU IMAGINE
DROPPING THAT AT A DINNER PARTY?
(laughs)

25:43.083 --> 25:45.041
WE SAVED TWO LIVES TODAY.
(laughs)

25:45.083 --> 25:48.041
I MEAN, WHO'S GONNA TOP THAT?
(laughs)

25:48.083 --> 25:50.041
YEAH.
WE'RE ALWAYS GOOD TOGETHER.

25:50.083 --> 25:53.875
WHEN IT'S JUST US...
WE'RE GREAT TOGETHER.

25:55.375 --> 25:57.375
BUT WE LIVE
IN THE REAL WORLD,

25:57.417 --> 26:02.041
AND IT'S TAKEN ME A WHILE,
BUT I'M--I'M OKAY WITH IT.

26:02.083 --> 26:03.917
WE'LL BE FRIENDS.

26:03.959 --> 26:06.375
WE'LL BE NEIGHBORS.

26:06.417 --> 26:09.458
BUT WE CAN NEVER
BE MORE THAN THAT.

26:14.834 --> 26:17.208
NAOMI TOLD ME THAT YOU'RE
REFUSING TO GIVE WILLIAM

26:17.250 --> 26:20.000
YOUR A.L.S. PROTOCOL.

26:20.041 --> 26:21.375
PROTECTING MY RESEARCH.

26:21.417 --> 26:24.000
ONE DAY, WHEN THIS DRUG
IS APPROVED BY THE F.D.A.

26:24.041 --> 26:26.041
AND SAVING THOUSANDS OF LIVES,

26:26.083 --> 26:28.041
NAOMI WILL REALIZE
IT WAS MORE IMPORTANT

26:28.083 --> 26:31.709
THAN THE LIFE OF JUST ONE MAN.
REALLY?
THAT'S YOUR REASON?

26:31.750 --> 26:34.125
BECAUSE IF IT IS, THAT'S GOOD.

26:34.166 --> 26:37.834
IF YOU'RE SAYING NO BECAUSE
YOU WANT TO GET NAOMI...

26:37.875 --> 26:40.500
MIND YOUR OWN BUSINESS.

26:40.542 --> 26:43.083
DOES SHE KNOW
THAT YOU'RE IN LOVE WITH HER?
OH, SCREW YOU.

26:43.125 --> 26:46.333
YOU'RE PATHETIC.
OH, COMING FROM THE GUY WHO
DRAGGED VIOLET THROUGH A TRIAL?

26:46.375 --> 26:49.041
I DIDN'T DRAG VIOLET THROUGH
A TRIAL. SHE DRAGGED ME.
YOU TURNED HER FRIENDS
AGAINST HER.

26:49.083 --> 26:52.041
ARE YOU KIDDING ME?
AND NOW YOU'RE KEEPING HER
AWAY FROM HER CHILD?

26:52.083 --> 26:55.041
YOU'RE GONNA CALL ME PATHETIC?
GO ON, HIT ME.

26:55.083 --> 26:58.041
YOU THINK I CAN'T TAKE
A PUNCH IN THE FACE?
YOU'RE NOT WORTH IT.

26:58.083 --> 27:01.000
YOU KNOW WHAT? I AM SO SICK
OF BEING THE GUY IN THE CHAIR.

27:01.041 --> 27:02.917
THE GUY IN THE CHAIR
NEVER GETS THE GIRL.

27:02.959 --> 27:04.959
AND THIS TIME,
I AM GETTING THE GIRL.

27:05.000 --> 27:06.959
SO SCREW THE CHAIR.
COME ON. HIT ME.

27:07.000 --> 27:09.000
WHO'S THE BIGGER MAN NOW, PETE?
COME ON.

27:09.041 --> 27:12.000
HIT ME.
YOU'RE LETTING WILLIAM DIE
SO YOU CAN HAVE NAOMI.

27:12.041 --> 27:15.583
THE CHAIR IS NOT
WHAT MAKES YOU THE SMALLER MAN.

27:22.166 --> 27:25.125
GET OUT.
NOT UNTIL YOU LISTEN
TO WHAT I HAVE TO SAY.

27:25.166 --> 27:27.750
OKAY, THEN I'LL GET OUT.
OKAY, WHEN YOU SENT SAM
INTO MY OFFICE

27:27.792 --> 27:30.041
THE FIRST WEEKS THAT WE
WORKED HERE TO FAKE FIRE ME

27:30.083 --> 27:32.500
FOR LOOKING AT ADULT WEB SITES
ON MY COMPUTER, I FORGAVE YOU.

27:32.542 --> 27:34.500
OH, COOPER. ARE YOU KID--
WHEN YOU TOLD ANNIE MERSEL,

27:34.542 --> 27:36.500
WHO I'M PRETTY SURE
I WAS FALLING IN LOVE WITH,

27:36.542 --> 27:38.542
THAT I WASN'T
THE MARRYING KIND BECAUSE

27:38.583 --> 27:42.000
YOU COULDN'T PICTURE US TOGETHER
IN 20 YEARS, I FORGAVE YOU.
COOPER--

27:42.041 --> 27:44.000
PUKING IN MY NEW CAR,
PUKING IN MY OLD BED

27:44.041 --> 27:46.834
OR USING THE 1910 SILVER DOLLAR
MY GRANDFATHER GAVE ME

27:46.875 --> 27:50.583
FOR MY BAR MITZVAH
TO PAY THE PIZZA GUY...

27:50.625 --> 27:53.083
BUT THAT'S WHAT FRIENDS DO.

27:53.125 --> 27:54.709
THEY SCREW UP,

27:54.750 --> 27:57.208
AND SOMETIMES,
THEY HURT EACH OTHER...

27:57.250 --> 27:59.333
AND YOU FORGIVE THEM.

27:59.375 --> 28:01.917
THAT'S WHAT FRIENDSHIP IS.

28:01.959 --> 28:04.375
THAT'S WHAT LOVE IS.

28:07.166 --> 28:09.583
I'M GOING TO LEAVE YOU NOW.

28:09.625 --> 28:12.000
BUT I LEAVE YOU WITH THIS...

28:12.041 --> 28:15.041
YOU ONCE TOLD A WOMAN
I HAD JUST STARTED DATING

28:15.083 --> 28:18.041
THAT I HAVE
A VERY SMALL NIGHTSTICK,

28:18.083 --> 28:20.667
WHICH WAS UNFORGIVABLE
AND ALSO...

28:20.709 --> 28:22.166
A LIE.

28:22.208 --> 28:34.250
AND I LET IT SLIDE.

28:34.291 --> 28:35.959
(monitor beeping rhythmically)

28:36.000 --> 28:37.333
MM.

28:37.375 --> 28:40.041
WHAT... WHAT HAPPENED?

28:40.083 --> 28:42.000
YOUR ANEURYSM RUPTURED,

28:42.041 --> 28:44.041
BUT WE WERE ABLE
TO REPAIR IT.

28:44.083 --> 28:46.041
MY BABY?
SHE'S DOING GREAT.

28:46.083 --> 28:48.041
KIM, WE SPOKE WITH THE FBI.

28:48.083 --> 28:50.041
THEY'RE TRYING TO TRACK DOWN
YOUR BIOLOGICAL PARENTS.

28:50.083 --> 28:52.166
WHERE'S GEORGE?
HE CAN'T HURT YOU.

28:52.208 --> 28:54.166
WE HAVE A POLICE OFFICER
STATIONED AT THE DOOR.

28:54.208 --> 28:56.041
YOU ARE SAFE HERE.

28:56.083 --> 28:57.792
NO.

28:57.834 --> 29:00.959
YOU DON'T UNDERSTAND.

29:01.000 --> 29:03.709
I NEED TO SEE HIM.

29:03.750 --> 29:05.625
I LOVE HIM.

29:10.291 --> 29:11.875
THE PROCEDURE WENT WELL.

29:11.917 --> 29:14.250
I'LL PROBABLY SEND CLAIRE HOME
IN A FEW DAYS.

29:14.291 --> 29:16.041
AND THE REST?
WE'LL SEE.

29:16.083 --> 29:19.083
(Claire) WHERE THE HELL
ARE THEY--THE DAMN DOCTORS?

29:19.125 --> 29:21.041
I AM TIRED OF WAITING.

29:21.083 --> 29:22.667
I'M SORRY.

29:22.709 --> 29:24.291
I CAN'T.

29:24.333 --> 29:26.083
CLAIRE.

29:26.125 --> 29:28.250
YOU LIED TO ME, YOU BITCH.

29:28.291 --> 29:32.667
YOU PUSHED ME TO DO THIS.
NOW I HAVE NOTHING. NOTHING!

29:32.709 --> 29:34.959
YOU SHOULDA
LET ME DIE HAPPY.

29:40.792 --> 29:42.750
(Addison) HE KIDNAPPED HER,
ASSAULTED HER

29:42.792 --> 29:44.750
AND KEPT HER
AWAY FROM HER REAL FAMILY,

29:44.792 --> 29:46.750
AND SHE STILL
WANTS TO SEE HIM?

29:46.792 --> 29:49.750
THE POLICE SAID GEORGE
HELD HER CAPTIVE FOR 15 YEARS.

29:49.792 --> 29:51.792
HE'S BEEN THE ONLY PERSON
IN HER LIFE,

29:51.834 --> 29:53.792
PUTTING CLOTHES ON HER BACK
AND FEEDING HER

29:53.834 --> 29:55.792
AND MAKING ALL THE DECISIONS
IN HER LIFE.

29:55.834 --> 29:57.792
TO HER,
HE IS HER REAL FAMILY.

29:57.834 --> 29:59.792
IT'S THE ONLY LOVE
SHE KNOWS.

29:59.834 --> 30:02.500
OH, IT'S JUST TOO PERVERSE
TO COMPREHEND.

30:02.542 --> 30:05.041
WELL, ALL KIM SEES
IS THAT HE TOOK CARE OF HER,

30:05.083 --> 30:06.542
PROTECTED HER.

30:06.583 --> 30:08.542
HAVE THEY LOCATED HER FAMILY,
HER PARENTS?

30:08.583 --> 30:10.250
I MEAN,
MAYBE WHEN SHE SEES THEM--

30:10.291 --> 30:12.250
SHE'S BEEN TOTALLY
CUT OFF FROM THE WORLD.

30:12.291 --> 30:14.250
AND OVER TIME,
THAT OLD LOVE SHE KNEW

30:14.291 --> 30:16.041
BECAME VAGUE, FADED MEMORIES.

30:16.083 --> 30:18.041
AND EVENTUALLY,
IN ORDER TO SURVIVE,

30:18.083 --> 30:20.000
HIS BELIEFS BECOME HER BELIEF

30:20.041 --> 30:22.083
AND HIS REALITY
BECOMES HER REALITY.

30:22.125 --> 30:24.125
(David Gray)
♪ ...SENSE OF LOSS ♪

30:24.166 --> 30:25.917
(metal clanks)

30:25.959 --> 30:29.041
♪ I'M THE MEMORY YOU CAN'T GET ♪

30:29.083 --> 30:30.625
♪ OUT YOUR HEAD ♪

30:30.667 --> 30:33.041
WAS THERE SOMETHING
YOU WANTED?

30:33.083 --> 30:35.333
♪ BUT IF I LEAVE YOU NOW ♪

30:35.375 --> 30:37.041
♪ YOU'LL WISH YOU WERE... ♪

30:37.083 --> 30:39.792
I WANT TO ASK YOU
TO FORGIVE ME.

30:39.834 --> 30:41.166
I MEAN--I MEAN, NOT NOW.

30:41.208 --> 30:45.000
I MEAN, I DON'T EXPECT YOU TO
FORGIVE ME RIGHT NOW, BUT...

30:45.041 --> 30:47.000
I RAN OUT ON YOU...

30:47.041 --> 30:49.417
WHEN I SHOULD'VE LEANED IN.

30:49.458 --> 30:53.625
I GAVE YOU MY BABY
AND... I RAN.

30:53.667 --> 30:55.625
AND PART OF IT'S NOT MY FAULT.

30:55.667 --> 30:57.667
PART OF IT'S
WHAT HAPPENED TO ME,

30:57.709 --> 31:00.208
BUT THERE'S THIS--
THERE'S THIS OTHER PIECE,

31:00.250 --> 31:01.834
AND...

31:01.875 --> 31:04.166
YOU LOVED ME.

31:04.208 --> 31:07.000
YOU LOVED ME...

31:07.041 --> 31:11.041
AND I SHOULD'VE
LEANED INTO THAT.

31:11.083 --> 31:13.875
I SHOULD'VE LET YOU
TAKE CARE OF ME.

31:13.917 --> 31:16.208
BUT I DIDN'T...

31:16.250 --> 31:18.250
BECAUSE...

31:18.291 --> 31:20.041
BECAUSE I DON'T KNOW HOW.

31:20.083 --> 31:22.041
(chuckles)

31:22.083 --> 31:24.041
YOU KNOW, I'M THAT PERSON.
I'M A SHRINK.

31:24.083 --> 31:26.041
I TAKE CARE OF OTHER PEOPLE,
BUT--

31:26.083 --> 31:30.667
AND I SHOULD'VE LET YOU
TAKE CARE OF ME...

31:30.709 --> 31:33.917
BUT I DIDN'T.

31:33.959 --> 31:36.917
SO WHEN I ASKED YOU
TO SHARE LUCAS WITH ME,

31:36.959 --> 31:38.917
OF COURSE YOU SAID NO.

31:38.959 --> 31:40.917
I-I SHOULDN'T HAVE BEEN HURT.

31:40.959 --> 31:43.000
I SHOULDN'T HAVE TAKEN YOU
TO COURT.

31:43.041 --> 31:46.000
I LOST MY HAPPINESS,

31:46.041 --> 31:48.417
AND I DIDN'T ASK FOR HELP.

31:48.458 --> 31:52.041
I DIDN'T LEAN IN.

31:52.083 --> 31:54.709
SO HOW COULD I POSSIBLY
EXPECT YOU

31:54.750 --> 31:57.250
TO LEAN INTO ME...

31:57.291 --> 32:00.667
TO... TO TRUST ME...

32:00.709 --> 32:02.417
TO BELIEVE IN ME?

32:02.458 --> 32:04.625
♪ ...OUT OF YOUR HAIR ♪

32:04.667 --> 32:07.041
AND SO I...

32:07.083 --> 32:08.959
♪ GOD HELP ME, BABY ♪

32:09.000 --> 32:10.750
I'M SORRY.

32:10.792 --> 32:13.041
♪ I'M LOST INSIDE ♪

32:13.083 --> 32:16.834
AND I UNDERSTAND.

32:16.875 --> 32:21.041
YOU DID WHAT YOU THOUGHT
WAS RIGHT.

32:21.083 --> 32:24.041
BUT I HOPE THAT SOMEDAY...

32:24.083 --> 32:26.208
YOU CAN FORGIVE ME.

32:26.250 --> 32:29.041
♪♪♪

32:29.083 --> 32:31.000
♪ YES ♪

32:33.792 --> 32:37.333
WE COULD START
WITH OVERNIGHT VISITS

32:37.375 --> 32:40.041
FOR LUCAS...

32:40.083 --> 32:43.083
♪♪♪

32:44.834 --> 32:47.583
UNTIL...

32:47.625 --> 32:49.041
HE GETS USED TO IT--

32:49.083 --> 32:51.041
UNTIL I GET USED TO IT--

32:51.083 --> 32:52.834
IF THAT'S OKAY.

32:56.041 --> 32:59.542
♪ I'M THE BABE THAT SLEEPS ♪

32:59.583 --> 33:03.375
♪ THROUGH THE BLITZ ♪

33:03.417 --> 33:07.041
♪ I AM A SUDDEN AND... ♪

33:07.083 --> 33:10.792
♪ QUITE UNEXPECTED TWIST ♪

33:10.834 --> 33:13.417
♪ I AM YOUR ONE TRUE LOVE ♪

33:13.458 --> 33:19.041
♪ WHO SLEEPS WITH SOMEONE ELSE ♪

33:19.083 --> 33:23.125
I WISH I HAD SAID NO TO YOU
FOR THE RIGHT REASONS.

33:23.166 --> 33:26.417
INSTEAD, I SAID NO
FOR THE WRONG ONES.

33:26.458 --> 33:28.041
♪ ...LIFE ITSELF ♪

33:28.083 --> 33:29.834
I'M IN LOVE WITH YOU.

33:29.875 --> 33:31.417
AND EVEN IF I WORK

33:31.458 --> 33:34.041
THE--THE POOR
CRIPPLED GUY ANGLE,

33:34.083 --> 33:37.417
I CAN'T COMPETE
WITH A DYING MAN.

33:37.458 --> 33:41.041
SO I SAID NO SO THAT
HE WOULD JUST DIE ALREADY

33:41.083 --> 33:43.083
AND BE OUT OF THE PICTURE.

33:43.125 --> 33:45.041
BUT THE THING IS,
I'M IN LOVE WITH YOU,

33:45.083 --> 33:47.041
AND WILLIAM DYING
WOULD HURT YOU.

33:47.083 --> 33:50.166
AND I CAN'T HURT YOU.
I CAN'T.

33:50.208 --> 33:54.792
IF YOU WANT SOMETHING,
I WANT TO GIVE IT TO YOU...

33:54.834 --> 33:57.333
BECAUSE YOU DESERVE
TO BE HAPPY.

33:57.375 --> 33:59.875
BECAUSE EVEN IF I HATE WILLIAM,

33:59.917 --> 34:03.667
I CAN'T BE HAPPY
UNLESS YOU'RE HAPPY.

34:03.709 --> 34:05.041
GABRIEL...

34:05.083 --> 34:06.875
I'M HAVING
THE PROTOCOL PREPARED.

34:06.917 --> 34:10.834
IT'LL BE HERE WITHIN THE HOUR
TO ADMINISTER TO WILLIAM.

34:10.875 --> 34:13.458
I'M SO VERY SORRY...

34:13.500 --> 34:15.041
ABOUT YOUR RESEARCH

34:15.083 --> 34:19.041
AND THE... COMPROMISE
I'M ASKING YOU TO MAKE.

34:19.083 --> 34:21.041
I HAD A CHOICE TO MAKE.

34:21.083 --> 34:24.166
I MADE IT
AND NOW I GOTTA LIVE WITH IT.

34:24.208 --> 34:26.834
I HOPE
YOU CAN LIVE WITH YOURS.

34:26.875 --> 34:29.875
♪♪♪

34:33.458 --> 34:36.417
(monitor beeping rhythmically)

34:36.458 --> 34:39.417
♪♪♪

34:39.458 --> 34:41.417
(woman speaks indistinctly
over p.a.)

34:41.458 --> 34:43.834
(cartoons playing indistinctly
on tv)

34:43.875 --> 34:48.208
I USED TO WATCH CARTOONS.

34:48.250 --> 34:50.208
I'D GET UP EARLY
ON SATURDAY MORNINGS

34:50.250 --> 34:53.834
AND SNEAK INTO THE LIVING ROOM.

34:53.875 --> 34:58.041
I KEPT THE VOLUME LOW
SO I WOULDN'T WAKE ANYONE UP.

34:58.083 --> 35:02.000
IT WAS THE ONLY DAY
MY MOM AND DAD GOT TO SLEEP IN.

35:04.583 --> 35:07.750
I FORGOT ABOUT CARTOONS.

35:09.792 --> 35:13.417
WELL... IN TIME, I'M SURE
THERE'LL BE LOTS OF THINGS

35:13.458 --> 35:15.041
THAT YOU'LL REMEMBER.

35:17.500 --> 35:19.250
HE LOVES ME, YOU KNOW?

35:19.291 --> 35:22.250
BUT SOMETIMES PEOPLE CONFUSE
OTHER THINGS FOR LOVE,

35:22.291 --> 35:25.166
LIKE...
NOT WANTING TO BE LONELY

35:25.208 --> 35:29.500
OR... AFRAID OR HURT.

35:31.083 --> 35:33.041
WE'RE HAVING A BABY TOGETHER.

35:33.083 --> 35:36.750
I KNOW. AND YOU'RE
GOING TO LOVE THAT BABY.

35:36.792 --> 35:39.333
BUT NOT WITH GEORGE,

35:39.375 --> 35:41.333
BECAUSE YOU DON'T WANT
YOUR DAUGHTER

35:41.375 --> 35:43.333
TO GO THROUGH
WHAT YOU WENT THROUGH,

35:43.375 --> 35:44.959
BECAUSE YOU DON'T WANT HIM

35:45.000 --> 35:47.041
TO DO TO YOUR DAUGHTER
WHAT HE DID TO YOU.

35:47.083 --> 35:49.000
BECAUSE THAT'S NOT LOVE.

35:53.834 --> 35:55.375
(woman speaking indistinctly
over p.a.)

35:55.417 --> 35:57.792
WHAT DO YOU WANT?

35:57.834 --> 35:59.750
JUST CHECKING UP ON YOU.

35:59.792 --> 36:01.875
I THOUGHT MAYBE WE COULD TALK.

36:01.917 --> 36:04.583
I WASTED THREE YEARS
OF MY LIFE TALKING TO YOU.

36:04.625 --> 36:06.083
I'M NOT WASTING ANYMORE.

36:06.125 --> 36:08.208
YOU'RE UNHAPPY.

36:08.250 --> 36:10.041
I CAN HELP YOU.

36:10.083 --> 36:12.041
I AM JUST SO TIRED
OF YOU HELPING ME.

36:12.083 --> 36:15.208
WHERE HAS IT GOTTEN ME,
HUH? LOOK AT ME.

36:15.250 --> 36:17.208
I'M HERE ALONE
IN A HOSPITAL ROOM

36:17.250 --> 36:19.375
WITH A--WITH A HOLE
IN MY HEAD.

36:21.083 --> 36:23.041
YOU DON'T HAVE TO BE ALONE.

36:23.083 --> 36:26.417
YOU HAVE HAD
A RARE EXPERIENCE, CLAIRE.

36:26.458 --> 36:30.125
YOU GOT TO LOOK THROUGH A DOOR
TO THE OTHER SIDE OF YOUR SOUL.

36:30.166 --> 36:32.959
AND NOW YOU'RE AFRAID.

36:33.000 --> 36:34.959
YOU'RE AFRAID THAT DOOR
IS CLOSED FOREVER.

36:35.000 --> 36:36.875
BUT IT ISN'T.

36:36.917 --> 36:38.875
IT'S--IT'S THERE
WAITING FOR YOU.

36:38.917 --> 36:43.709
YOU JUST HAVE TO FIND A WAY
TO WALK THROUGH IT.

36:46.083 --> 36:49.041
HOW DO YOU SUGGEST
I DO THAT?

36:49.083 --> 36:51.041
WE CAN TRY NEW THINGS,

36:51.083 --> 36:53.625
ALTERNATIVE THERAPIES.

36:53.667 --> 36:56.417
AND WE'D DO IT TOGETHER.

36:56.458 --> 36:58.667
I'M AFRAID.

37:01.291 --> 37:03.417
I KNOW.

37:08.125 --> 37:09.458
(knock on door)

37:09.500 --> 37:12.083
HEY.
WHAT TOOK YOU SO LONG?
I CALLED AN HOUR AGO.

37:12.125 --> 37:15.041
I CAME AS SOON AS YOU CALLED.
WHERE'S DINK?
BAND PRACTICE.
HE CAN'T HEAR HIS CELL.

37:15.083 --> 37:18.625
CORINNE?
SHE WENT TO SAN FRANCISCO
TO VISIT A SICK AUNT.

37:18.667 --> 37:21.041
SHE LEFT YOU HERE ALONE?
MY DUE DATE'S
NOT FOR THREE WEEKS.

37:21.083 --> 37:25.000
SHE DIDN'T THINK I'D--
OH, MY GOD. THAT HURTS.
WELL, YOU'RE DEFINITELY
IN LABOR.

37:25.041 --> 37:27.667
OKAY, I'LL TAKE YOU
TO THE BIRTHING SUITE.
I WANT TO GO TO THE HOSPITAL.

37:27.709 --> 37:30.041
THAT'S NOT A PART OF THE PLAN.
SCREW THE PLAN.

37:30.083 --> 37:31.291
MAYA--
I'M NOT WAITING HERE!

37:31.333 --> 37:32.583
I WANT TO GO TO THE HOSPITAL
LIKE A NORMAL PERSON

37:32.625 --> 37:34.583
WHERE THEY HAVE DOCTORS
AND PAIN MEDICINE.

37:34.625 --> 37:37.041
SO GET YOUR KEYS
AND LET'S GO NOW.

37:46.291 --> 37:49.333
(wheelchair motor whirs)

37:50.917 --> 37:53.125
(door opens)

37:53.166 --> 37:54.250
OKAY?

38:00.875 --> 38:02.417
LAINEY?

38:02.458 --> 38:04.166
LAINEY?

38:06.083 --> 38:09.166
L-- (crying)

38:16.041 --> 38:19.000
(continues crying)

38:22.333 --> 38:25.166
YOU THINK SHE'LL EVER
GET OVER SOMETHING LIKE THAT?

38:25.208 --> 38:26.792
HOW COULD SHE?

38:26.834 --> 38:28.166
I MEAN, RIGHT OR WRONG,

38:28.208 --> 38:30.959
SHE JUST LOST
THE ONLY PERSON SHE LOVES.

38:31.000 --> 38:32.792
(cell phone rings and beeps)

38:32.834 --> 38:34.375
HEY, DELL.

38:34.417 --> 38:37.166
WHAT--HOLD ON.
SHE WANTS ME TO DELIVER...

38:37.208 --> 38:39.041
OH, OKAY.

38:39.083 --> 38:41.500
HOW--HOW FAR APART
ARE HER CONTRACTIONS?

38:41.542 --> 38:43.083
IS THAT--IS IT M--

38:43.125 --> 38:44.792
OKAY.

38:44.834 --> 38:47.834
UH, YEAH, T-TELL HER THAT
WE WILL MEET HER AT THE E.R.

38:47.875 --> 38:50.959
AND, UM, AND T-TELL HER
THAT WE LOVE HER, DELL.

38:51.000 --> 38:53.125
(laughs) OKAY. YEAH.
DRIVE SAFELY.

38:53.166 --> 38:54.750
BYE.
(beep)

38:54.792 --> 38:55.834
(laughs)

38:55.875 --> 38:57.834
SO IT'S, UH, IT'S HAPPENING.
(laughs)

38:57.875 --> 39:01.208
THIS IS HAPPENING. OH.

39:01.250 --> 39:02.834
(chuckles)

39:02.875 --> 39:05.208
UH, I HAVE TO GO DELIVER
YOUR GRANDCHILD.
YES. YES, YOU DO.

39:05.250 --> 39:06.625
(laughs)

39:06.667 --> 39:09.417
OW! OH.
WE'RE ALMOST THERE.

39:09.458 --> 39:11.458
OH, OW!

39:13.750 --> 39:15.083
HEY, W--
HEY.

39:15.125 --> 39:16.625
WHAT'S SO IMPORTANT?

39:16.667 --> 39:20.250
I HAVE... MACARONI AND CHEESE
WITH SUGAR ON TOP,

39:20.291 --> 39:22.667
EGGPLANT PARM, EXTRA SPICY,

39:22.709 --> 39:24.041
STRAIGHT FROM TANA'S,

39:24.083 --> 39:26.041
I HAVE PUMPKIN PIE,
WHICH IS ACTUALLY

39:26.083 --> 39:28.542
INCREDIBLY HARD TO GET
THIS TIME OF YEAR,

39:28.583 --> 39:30.542
AND I HAVE THAT
SWEET SUGAR CANE STUFF

39:30.583 --> 39:34.041
THAT WE DRANK
IN THE SAN JOSE AIRPORT

39:34.083 --> 39:37.458
THAT WE DIDN'T KNOW WAS ALCOHOL
BUT MADE US INCREDIBLY DIZZY.
GUARO!

39:37.500 --> 39:40.875
GUARO! (laughs)
GUARO!

39:40.917 --> 39:43.291
(whispers) OKAY.

39:47.166 --> 39:49.041
(sighs)

39:49.083 --> 39:50.458
NOW...

39:50.500 --> 39:52.041
(sniffs)

39:52.083 --> 39:53.709
TALK TO ME ABOUT CHARLOTTE.

39:58.083 --> 40:00.625
YOU KNOW WHAT?
CAN WE JUST EAT?

40:00.667 --> 40:03.375
I SAW HER LEAVING
WITH SHELDON.

40:03.417 --> 40:06.041
SHE WAS DRESSED UP.

40:06.083 --> 40:07.917
HMM.

40:07.959 --> 40:10.750
DO YOU LOVE HER?

40:13.083 --> 40:15.834
THEN GO GET HER.

40:15.875 --> 40:19.208
(exhales)

40:19.250 --> 40:21.208
NOW, COOPER.

40:21.250 --> 40:23.583
I MEAN GO GET HER NOW.

40:23.625 --> 40:25.667
OH!

40:25.709 --> 40:27.834
OH.

40:27.875 --> 40:29.500
ALL RIGHT.
(clinks glasses)

40:29.542 --> 40:32.625
(Youth Group's "In My Dreams"
playing)

40:32.667 --> 40:35.834
(siren wailing)

40:35.875 --> 40:37.417
OKAY.

40:37.458 --> 40:39.834
(wailing continues)

40:39.875 --> 40:42.834
♪♪♪

40:42.875 --> 40:44.208
NAOMI WILL BE HERE SOON.

40:44.250 --> 40:45.834
THAT'S GOOD.

